**Deploy workflow:** always in this order: (1) test locally, (2) push to GitHub, (3) deploy to Fornex, (4) verify on Fornex. Never skip local testing or deploy without it.

Split tasks into phases: each phase is a separate chat; output of each phase is a concise markdown summary for the next phase.
Pick the right model for each phase: use cheap models for context prep and housekeeping, smart models for planning, architecture, and complex code.
One chat per phase: finish a phase, copy the markdown summary, start a new chat with it as input.
Code style: write code without comments. Use clear names, simple logic, no redundant comments or decorative explanations.
Answer briefly and to the point, until I ask you to explain in detail.
